  "lastUpdatedOn": "2012-11-05",
  "religion": "Wood is a Catholic, but we're not sure how devout.",
  "politicalViews": "Wood is a liberal and slightly radical.",
  "author": "Tom Kershaw",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 1
    },
    {
      "parentId": 1,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Elijah Wood was born and raised in Ceder Rapids, Iowa."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 2
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Wood was raised a Catholic.",
      "sourceTitle": "Elijah Wood",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.nndb.com/people/765/000022699/"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 2,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " But we get the feeling it wasn't an overwhelming, guilt-ridden Catholic upbringing like, say, the one Carlos Santana describes. He once said:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 3
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 4,
      "parentId": 3
    },
    {
      "parentId": 4,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I was raised Catholic. Well, not that my mother wanted to make a priest out of me or anything. You could call me a Catholic light.",
      "sourceTitle": "Elijah Wood",
      "sourceUrl": "http://always.ejwsites.net/HumoInterview.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 5
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "There's rumor that Wood is quite devout as an adult, even reports that he prays every night.",
      "sourceTitle": "Catholic Celebrity Awards",
      "sourceUrl": "http://bridgetbatson.hubpages.com/hub/Catholic-Celebrity-Awards"
    },
    {
      "parentId": 5,
      "type": "text",
      "text": " But I was unable to confirm that and given the fact that there's very little about Catholicism–or any religion for that matter–from Wood himself, it's a safe bet that he's either not religious or he keeps it to himself.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "id": 6
    },
    {
      "parentId": 6,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Elven politics"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 7
    },
    {
      "parentId": 7,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Woods is clearly a liberal–and not in the \"I'm a Hollywood star doing what all of the other Hollywood stars are doing\" sort of way. And he might even be a bit of a populist and slightly radical."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 8
    },
    {
      "parentId": 8,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "He's never endorsed Obama that I can see, but he did hop on Twitter to applaud the president for his stance on gay marriage, saying:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 9
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 10,
      "parentId": 9
    },
    {
      "parentId": 10,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Obama announces support for same-sex marriage. Well said, sir. Equality is the key word.",
      "sourceTitle": "Woodelijah: Obama announces support for…",
      "sourceUrl": "https://twitter.com/woodelijah/status/200567913818767360"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 11
    },
    {
      "parentId": 11,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Plus, he supports the legalization of marijuana. Even though he's not a pot smoker himself, Wood said:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 12
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 13,
      "parentId": 12
    },
    {
      "parentId": 13,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I think the whole notion that marijuana is illegal is past the point of ridiculousness.",
      "sourceTitle": "Elijah Wood Covers \"High Times\"; Talks Marijuana Support",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2011/08/23/elijah-wood-covers-high-t_n_934474.html"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 14
    },
    {
      "parentId": 14,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "More telling is Wood's stance on government and his support for the Occupy Wall Street movement. He was a promoter for a coalition called the 99 Percent Spring which brought together a wide range of groups to train and educate tens of thousands of people to be more effective agitators. It wasn't much of a success, apparently, and most Occupiers didn't back the project.",
      "sourceTitle": "Occupy Wall Street Activists Respond to the 99 Percent Spring",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.thenation.com/blog/167253/occupy-wall-street-activists-respond-99-spring#"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 15
    },
    {
      "parentId": 15,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "Still, Woods showed his share of solidarity. Stating his stance on public protests and political statements in general, Woods said:"
    },
    {
      "type": "quote",
      "id": 16
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": 17,
      "parentId": 16
    },
    {
      "parentId": 17,
      "type": "text",
      "text": "I always think it is important to question even your government, especially your government actually.",
      "sourceTitle": "Elijah Wood: Return of the RING",
      "sourceUrl": "http://www.mania.com/elijah-wood-return-ring_article_37226.html"
    }
  ],
